===Base Attack Time Manipulation===

There are a few abilities that can alter the base attack time of a unit, either by directly setting the unit's BAT to a fixed value or by reducing it by a certain amount.
Base attack time setting abilities do not stack with another and the first cast (or passively leveled) BAT setting ability has a higher precedence, even if another BAT setting ability with a lower BAT value gets used afterwards.

The only exceptions to this are {{A|Terrorblade|Metamorphosis}} and {{A|Kez|Switch Discipline}}, which always override other BAT setting abilities once cast or passively acquired, the latter having the highest priority of all BAT setting abilities.

Meanwhile base attack time reducing abilities fully stack with each other (except for {{A|Oracle|False Promise}} and {{A|Broodmother|Insatiable Hunger}}) and they also stack with the base attack time setting ability of the highest precedence. The order of stacking a BAT reducing and BAT setting ability does not matter, as BAT reducing abilities will always reduce a unit's current BAT after it was set to a fixed value by BAT setting abilities.

